    <!-- Project Modals -->
    <!-- Modal 1 -->
    <div class="modal" id="projectModal1">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="modal-close">&times;</span>
            <div class="modal-img">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1611915387288-fd8d2f5f928b?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Urban Sprawl Analysis">
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <h2>Urban Sprawl Analysis Using Landsat Data</h2>
                <p>This project analyzed urban expansion patterns in Metro City over a 20-year period (2000-2020) using Landsat satellite imagery. The study aimed to understand the drivers of urban growth and predict future expansion areas to inform sustainable urban planning policies.</p>
                
                <h3>Key Objectives</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Quantify the rate and direction of urban expansion</li>
                    <li>Identify land use/land cover changes</li>
                    <li>Model future growth scenarios</li>
                    <li>Assess environmental impacts of urban sprawl</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Methodology</h3>
                <p>The project utilized Landsat 5, 7, and 8 imagery with a temporal resolution of 5 years. Supervised classification was performed using ArcGIS Pro's Image Classification toolbar. Change detection analysis was conducted using the Post-Classification Comparison method. The SLEUTH urban growth model was implemented to predict future scenarios.</p>
                
                <h3>Results</h3>
                <p>The analysis revealed a 78% increase in urban area over the study period, with the most significant expansion occurring in the northern and western sectors. Agricultural lands decreased by 32%, while forest cover decreased by 15%. The model predicted a 40% additional urban expansion by 2040 under current trends.</p>
                
                <h3>Technologies Used</h3>
                <div class="project-tools">
                    <span class="project-tool">ArcGIS Pro</span>
                    <span class="project-tool">Landsat</span>
                    <span class="project-tool">Python</span>
                    <span class="project-tool">SLEUTH Model</span>
                    <span class="project-tool">NDVI Analysis</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Modal 2 -->
    <div class="modal" id="projectModal2">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="modal-close">&times;</span>
            <div class="modal-img">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581093196276-6357ffb6ddf7?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Flood Risk Assessment">
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <h2>Coastal Flood Risk Assessment</h2>
                <p>Comprehensive flood risk analysis for coastal communities integrating LiDAR elevation data, historical rainfall patterns, and sea level rise projections. The project produced flood hazard maps for various return periods and recommended mitigation strategies.</p>
                
                <h3>Key Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>1m resolution LiDAR-derived DEM</li>
                    <li>Integration of climate change scenarios</li>
                    <li>Hydraulic modeling of storm surge events</li>
                    <li>
